jobs_results.description:
Reporting to the Head of iOS Engineering, you, as iOS Developer — collaborating closely with our Product, Design, and QA teams —, will be contributing to spec, build, test and deploy new features on the GoodBarber engine — used to create thousands of apps.

Your role will involve developing digital product experiences and utilities for mobile and desktop, using the iOS SDK. You'll also be contributing by implementing best practices to ensure app reliability and security, fixing bugs, and refactoring the code base when necessary. You will build new features and enhance existing ones. You'll be able to proactively look for ways to make the project better.

Without you, we wouldn't be able to build the excellent experiences our users expect from us.

It's a big challenge, but no one said building great things was going to be easy. However, it does help that you will be doing this alongside great teammates, experienced enough to know the ropes, but young enough to believe we can change everything!

Missions & Responsibilities
• Craft new and improved features of the GoodBarber Engine;
• Analyse functional specifications (written by the functional project manager) and contribute to technical specifications (under the management of the technical lead);
• Identify the right technical solutions, define the technical architecture for given projects, within the general framework;
• Rapidly solve problems;
• Optimize the existing code for ease of use and performance;
• Prototype product concepts.

Why you should apply:
• An international environment. Be part of our multicultural and distributed team. Including regular trips to Ajaccio where you’ll be able to meet with our other offices.
• Transparency. Regular feedback, honest discussions about our company goals, and more.
• Impact. Create and develop a product that has a real impact on society.
• People-first. Fun, happy and politics-free work culture built on the principles of lean and self-organisation.
• Shared company principles that guide us in our everyday decision-making and bring us closer to our goal.
• We'll provide you with a Macbook and the tech stack to help you do your best work.
• Flexible work hours.
• Health Insurance.
• Meal allowance.
• 25 days of vacation.
• A fair & competitive salary package.

What you might bring:
• 1y+ of experience with iOS SDK,
• Strong communication skills (English), comfortable working with teams from diverse backgrounds;
• Collaborative attitude when working with other team members;
• Strong problem solving skills;
• The ability to propose, listen and accept constructive feedback;
• Bias-to-action, you’re autonomous and unafraid to be proactive;
• Experience with agile software development lifecycle (Scrum);
• Experience using project management tools (JIRA, Confluence.

About Us

Agentifai is building the most advanced AI assistants with new interaction models and state-of-the-art technology. We exist to reinvent the way people access the most important services in their lives, such as Healthcare or Financial services.

For the first time, it’s the technology that adapts to humans and not vice-versa. Our mission is to change the relationship between humans and machines by using one of the oldest human tools: language.

We are looking for talented people to humanize technology.

Join us to create this Exponential Experience.

Job Description

We’re looking for talented iOS Developers to:

Design, develop, our mobile framework/SDK for the iOS platform. Apply best coding practices and advocate for them through design and code reviews. Collaborate and brainstorm across teams to define and ship new features.

What we are looking for
• Bachelor’s or Master's Degree in Software Engineering, Computer Science, or similar. If you don’t have it but you understand computer science and software engineering fundamentals, we still want to hear from you;
• Deep knowledge of Swift and the iOS SDK.
• Understanding of UIKit and Auto Layout.
• Understanding of reactive programming (RxSwift, Combine, etc).
• Creating fluid visual interactions, creating and implementing mobile user experience patterns;
• Keeping up with the latest trends, architectures, ideas and technologies in the mobile ecosystem;
• Producing clean and organized code, taking advantage of software design patterns, architectural patterns and data structures;

Nice to have

You don’t need to have knowledge in all of the following items, but you have in at least one of them, it will be a bonus:
• Be familiar with the user experience design process;
• Knowledge with CI/CD development methodologies and tools;

What can you expect from Agentifai
• In Agentifai you will have the opportunity to work on bleeding edge technology that is being applied in real world contexts in ways that have never been attempted before, namely text and voice enabled conversational agents with transactional capabilities (e.g. scheduling a medical appointment, performing a bank transfer, etc);
• You will be conceiving solutions for interesting problems which will improve your creativity and skillset as a software engineer;
• You will be part of an extremely skilled team working in a cordial and welcoming environment.
• Health insurance, flexible working and other benefits;
• Full Remote or Hybrid Work;

• Development of new features or new app’s;
• Maintenance of our existing and future IOS applications;
• Code review;
• Participation in all the development and delivery process;
• Writing unit tests.

• At least 7 years of experience on iOS development with a very good level of app architecture (Swift, SwiftUI, acessibility ...).
• Use of continuous integration tools / Git.
• Good level of English.

The Devoteam Group works for equal opportunities, promoting its employees based on merit and actively fights against all forms of discrimination. We are convinced that diversity contributes to the creativity, dynamism and excellence of our organization. All of our vacancies are open to people with disabilities.
